          "marks": [
            {
              "type": "code"
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "type": "text",
          "text": " is designed to validate reading codes from an uploaded file against a reference table. Specifically, it checks if all reading codes present in the "
        },
        {
          "type": "text",
          "text": "ConEd.UploadConEdisonMeter",
          "marks": [
            {
              "type": "code"
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "type": "text",
          "text": " table are also present in the "
        },
        {
          "type": "text",
          "text": "Billing.UtilityReadingCode",
          "marks": [
            {
              "type": "code"
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "type": "text",
          "text": " table for a specific utility company (identified by "
        },
        {
          "type": "text",
          "text": "UtilityCompanySeqid = 9",
          "marks": [
            {
              "type": "code"
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "type": "text",
          "text": "). If any reading code from the uploaded data is not found in the reference table, the procedure raises an error with a specific message."
        }
      ]
